 data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104eqw1665702639578.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eqw1665702639578.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eqw1665702639578.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"eqw1665702639578\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      No Display Character\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This property specifies the ASCII character to be displayed when text is entered that should not be echoed, for example, in a password field.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eqw1665702639578__section_epc_bc3_zwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1059373e51\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eqw1665702639578__p_d106043e1_d106044e1_d106045e1\">This property is only relevant when the\n          <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Syntax</span> definition includes NDI.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eqw1665702639578__p_d106046e1_d106047e1_d106048e1\">Enter the decimal value of the ASCII character to be\n        displayed as text is entered or click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">...</span> to select a character. The\n        specified character you enter here is the character that Uniface echoes to the edit box\n        instead of the entered text. The default value is a bullet (decimal 165).</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eqw1665702639578__section_ewf_cc3_zwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1059373e69\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"eqw1665702639578__ul_aqg_dc3_zwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eqw1665702639578__li_d42032e1_d42033e1_d42034e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"klb1688454363706.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/klb1688454363706.html\" title=\"Default logical widget for entering and displaying data in a field in a Form or Report.\">EditBox</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eqw1665702639578__li_d42035e1_d42036e1_d42037e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qwk1688451210612.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qwk1688451210612.html\" title=\"The urtfeditbox widget is used to display and edit text as Rich Text Format (RTF), which supports formatting such as font and color attributes, text alignment, indentation, and lists. Uniface provides a logical widget called RichEditBox, which is mapped to urtfeditbox.\">urtfeditbox (RichEditBox)</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612854\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612854\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "No Display Character Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 No Display Character This property specifies the ASCII character to be displayed when text is entered that should not be echoed, for example, in a password field. Description This property is only relevant when the Field Syntax definition includes NDI. Enter the decimal value of the ASCII character to be displayed as text is entered or click ... to select a character. The specified character you enter here is the character that Uniface echoes to the edit box instead of the entered text. The default value is a bullet (decimal 165). Applies To EditBox urtfeditbox (RichEditBox) Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}